The paper focuses on self-supervised learning of video and audio representations, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method proposed in the paper involves clustering of audio and video data, which falls under the sub-category of unsupervised learning (cs.SD). The paper also deals with multi-modal learning, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
